Author: Birdie49
Text: I feel the exact same way. Whenever I let someone else bring me food (lmao sounds so entitled, I know, but I mean more that I prefer to get my own food), I am *meticulous* about telling them exactly what to get, because I've planned for it and counted it and if it's wrong I can't eat it. Eating disorders tend to cause us to have strong emotions around food, it seems.
